{"date": "2019-02-22", "title": "Saint Vincent and the Grenadines Honorary Consul in Australia", "content": "The Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Trade and Commerce welcomes its newly appointed Honorary Consul of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, Mr. Michele B.R. Dal Pra, a national of Australia.\n\nMr. Michele B.R. Dal Pra, in capacity of Honorary Consul for Saint Vincent and the Grenadines in Sydney, Australia, have consular jurisdiction throughout New South Wales, Queensland and Victoria to provide services to Vincentian nationals living in Australia. Further, as Honorary Consul, Mr. Dal Pra will undertake to develop cultural ties between Saint Vincent and the Grenadines and Australia, assist with consular services, develop bilateral trading links, expand educational opportunities for Vincentians and promote tourism and industry.\nThe Honorary Consulate in Sydney, Australia, is located at 130 Mount Vernon Road, Mount Vernon, NSW 2178 and can be contacted at This email address is being protected from spambots. You need JavaScript enabled to view it..\n\u00a0\n\u00a0\n\u00a0\nSOURCE: Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Trade and Commerce", "id": "c8984310d83036df98f7f64ee580d648"}
{"date": "2015-03-10", "title": "His Excellency Jeroen Willem De Graaf presented his Letters of Credence", "content": "On Thursday March 5, 2015 the new Non-resident Ambassador of the Kingdom of the Netherlands to Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, His Excellency Jeroen Willem De Graaf, resident in Trinidad and Tobago, presented his Letters of Credence to His Excellency Sir Frederick Ballantyne, Governor General of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines at Government House.\nIn addition to his meeting with the Governor General, Ambassador De Graaf made a courtesy call on the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Foreign Trade, Commerce and Information Technology, Senator the Hon. Camillo Gonsalves. Moreover, the Ambassador was given an extensive tour of the Argyle International Airport site.Ambassador De Graaf also serves as Non-resident Ambassador of the Kingdom of the Netherlands to other members of the Organisation of Eastern Caribbean States (OECS) and to Barbados. His posting to the region is his first assignment as an Ambassador of the Netherlands.Saint Vincent and the Grenadines and the Kingdom of Netherlands established diplomatic relations on the April 8, 1981.", "id": "c8ca9b3adb543461b908fe3b5110f06d"}
