{"date": "2019-07-12", "title": "President Tsai's Journey of Freedom, Democracy, Sustainability \u2013 Caribbean Region Tour", "content": "Her Excellency Tsai Ing-wen, President of the Republic of China (Taiwan), is scheduled to visit Saint Vincent and the Grenadines for a two-day state visit from July 16 \u2013 17, 2019; as part of a Caribbean region tour, which has been deemed as \u201cPresident Tsai Ing-Wen Journey of Freedom, Democracy, Sustainability \u2013 Haiti, St. Kitts and Nevis, Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, and St. Lucia\u201d.\nPresident Tsai Ing-wen's tour of the region is aimed at further strengthening cooperation, exchanges and friendship, between Taiwan and its four (4) Caribbean allies. In Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, President Tsai will hold talks with Prime Minister, Dr. The Hon. Ralph E. Gonsalves.\nPresident Tsai\u2019s delegation will comprise of high level government officials, as well as legislators and business representatives. The trip is her first to the region as Head of State, and seventh abroad since assuming office in May, 2016.\n\u00a0\u00a0\nSOURCE: Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Trade & Commerce", "id": "ff85a005cc343a9684af76248c08d20a"}
